WEBVTT

01:39.266 --> 01:40.535
Ooh.

01:57.719 --> 01:59.252
Fuck.

02:17.572 --> 02:18.706
Uhh!

02:33.855 --> 02:34.822
Unh!

02:34.856 --> 02:36.791
Ahh!

02:41.729 --> 02:43.263
Fuck!

02:48.770 --> 02:50.838
Ah, fuck!

03:11.391 --> 03:13.460
Ah! Ahh!

04:01.943 --> 04:03.644
<i>Well done, you...</i>

04:05.445 --> 04:07.380
<i>Well done. You're the winner.</i>

04:07.582 --> 04:10.417
<i>Remind me. Are you the original
or the double?</i>

04:14.454 --> 04:15.523
<i>The double.</i>

04:16.591 --> 04:18.926
<i>Of course.
I always get mixed up.</i>

04:18.959 --> 04:22.362
<i>Obviously it gets confusing
when you both look identical.</i>

04:22.730 --> 04:24.832
<i>Excellent work negating
his ranged attack</i>

04:24.866 --> 04:26.601
<i>and closing the distance.</i>

04:29.704 --> 04:30.872
<i>Thank you.</i>

04:32.874 --> 04:34.809
<i>The double has won the duel.</i>

04:35.442 --> 04:36.944
<i>He's Robert Michaels now.</i>

04:55.863 --> 04:57.865
<i>Can I take your order?</i>

04:57.899 --> 05:00.535
Yes, I'll have
one two-layer taco,

05:00.568 --> 05:02.703
two soft tacos,

05:02.737 --> 05:05.540
a double burrito,
and an order of nachos.

05:05.573 --> 05:06.841
<i>WHICH ONE?</i>

05:06.874 --> 05:08.509
<i>We have several kinds of nachos.</i>

05:08.543 --> 05:10.611
The one that's just
the chips and cheese dip.

05:10.645 --> 05:12.680
<i>How many drinks for this order?</i>

05:12.713 --> 05:14.414
Only one.

05:41.642 --> 05:43.611
<i>I don't know. It's haunted.</i>

05:43.878 --> 05:45.847
<i>But look, there's a pool.</i>

05:49.684 --> 05:51.519
<i>Yeah, yeah!</i>

05:51.552 --> 05:52.920
<i>Oh, yeah!</i>

06:20.948 --> 06:22.683
Well, hello.

06:22.717 --> 06:24.852
<i>Hey, sweetheart.
What are you up to?</i>

06:24.886 --> 06:26.587
Just watching television.

06:26.621 --> 06:27.822
<i>What are you watching?</i>

06:30.825 --> 06:33.628
A reality competition
show about dating.

06:33.661 --> 06:35.563
<i>That doesn't sound very good.</i>

06:35.596 --> 06:38.065
It isn't very good, but
I consider it a guilty pleasure.

06:38.099 --> 06:39.867
What are you doing?

06:39.901 --> 06:42.536
<i>I took my team out
for drinks after work tonight.</i>

06:42.570 --> 06:44.805
<i>They've been doing such
a great job on this project.</i>

06:44.839 --> 06:46.574
What about
that co-worker of yours

06:46.607 --> 06:48.676
you were telling me about? Sam?

06:48.709 --> 06:50.678
Is he still struggling
with the workload?

06:50.711 --> 06:53.547
<i>Actually, Sam's doing
tremendous now.</i>

06:53.581 --> 06:55.549
Oh. Oh, that's good, I guess.

06:55.583 --> 06:57.585
<i>In fact, I'm even
considering giving him</i>

06:57.618 --> 06:59.053
<i>a most-improved award.</i>

06:59.086 --> 07:00.766
<i>Awards in the workplace
have been proven...</i>

07:05.860 --> 07:07.561
<i>increase morale even if it-if...</i>

07:07.595 --> 07:09.530
<i>it d-d-d...
Really mean anything.</i>

07:12.900 --> 07:14.568
I miss you.

07:16.003 --> 07:17.838
<i>I miss you, too, sweetheart.</i>

07:18.873 --> 07:20.908
<i>Maybe I'll call you
one more time before bed?</i>

07:20.942 --> 07:22.610
No, that's okay.

07:22.643 --> 07:24.612
I actually think I'm going
to go to bed soon, too.

07:24.645 --> 07:26.647
<i>Really? It's so early there.</i>

07:26.681 --> 07:27.982
Yes, but I'm tired.

07:32.620 --> 07:34.789
<i>All right, well, you should
definitely get some rest,</i>

07:34.822 --> 07:36.090
<i>and we can talk tomorrow.</i>

07:37.858 --> 07:39.760
I'll text you when I wake up.

07:39.794 --> 07:41.762
<i>All right. Good night, Sarah.</i>

07:59.180 --> 08:02.883
<i>Yes, yes, yes, yes, yes!</i>

08:02.917 --> 08:04.852
Sarah, dear,
are you really hungry?

08:04.885 --> 08:06.620
Or are you putting food
into your mouth

08:06.654 --> 08:08.122
so you don't have to talk to me?

08:08.923 --> 08:10.925
I'm just a normal
amount of hungry.

08:11.625 --> 08:14.095
It's possible to eat and have
a conversation at the same time.

08:16.063 --> 08:17.898
- I think I'm going to be...
- Sarah...

08:26.140 --> 08:27.942
I think I'm going to be
late for work.

08:27.975 --> 08:31.145
You don't have work today.
That's why you're here with me.

08:31.178 --> 08:33.080
What day is it?

08:33.114 --> 08:35.049
Do you remember these?

08:35.082 --> 08:36.884
My penny collection?

08:36.917 --> 08:38.719
Why did you stop collecting?

08:39.153 --> 08:41.589
I was 10, I took
on other hobbies.

08:41.621 --> 08:42.722
Where did you find these?

08:42.756 --> 08:44.592
Why aren't you happy anymore?

08:46.093 --> 08:47.595
I am happy.

08:47.628 --> 08:49.096
Why don't you answer my calls?

08:55.970 --> 08:57.705
Why don't you visit me?

09:00.875 --> 09:02.143
Don't you love me?

09:23.097 --> 09:24.632
Goodbye, Sarah.

10:42.877 --> 10:46.947
Ma'am, I said, is it
an emergency, or can you wait?

10:48.949 --> 10:50.784
No, it's not an emergency.

10:52.186 --> 10:55.789
Fill out as much of this form
as you can, initial this,

10:55.823 --> 10:57.583
and the yellow page
gives us permission to...

11:03.364 --> 11:06.267
Ma'am, I thought you said
this wasn't an emergency.

11:10.871 --> 11:12.339
<i>How are you feeling?</i>

11:12.373 --> 11:15.209
I'm feeling okay.
I haven't had any more episodes.

11:15.242 --> 11:17.077
<i>That's good news.</i>

11:17.111 --> 11:20.014
<i>Does this mean
you'll be coming home early?</i>

11:20.848 --> 11:22.783
<i>You know I can't
do that, sweetheart.</i>

11:23.117 --> 11:25.786
<i>We're at a very critical stage
of the project.</i>

11:26.220 --> 11:28.956
No, I know. I just
thought you might be able to...

11:28.989 --> 11:30.791
step away for a moment.

11:30.824 --> 11:32.259
<i>Perhaps.</i>

11:32.293 --> 11:34.261
<i>I need to figure
some things out here first.</i>

11:34.962 --> 11:36.397
I understand.

11:38.399 --> 11:40.834
<i>Hey, what did
the gastroenterologist say?</i>

11:41.268 --> 11:43.103
She's still running tests.

11:43.370 --> 11:45.239
Everyone is having
a hard time believing me

11:45.272 --> 11:48.008
that there were no signs
or symptoms leading up to this.

11:50.411 --> 11:51.979
Who was that?

11:52.246 --> 11:53.914
<i>Aw, nothing. It was just...</i>

11:53.948 --> 11:56.016
<i>Sam texted me
that he got home safely.</i>

11:56.283 --> 11:58.185
You went out with
your co-workers tonight?

11:58.886 --> 12:00.287
<i>No, no, no. Just Sam.</i>

12:01.155 --> 12:03.023
<i>He accidentally drank
too much, though.</i>

12:03.057 --> 12:04.992
<i>I sent him home in a taxi.</i>

12:06.126 --> 12:07.928
<i>What are you up to tonight?</i>

12:10.931 --> 12:12.866
I'm in the hospital.

12:12.900 --> 12:15.436
<i>Right, right... I mean...</i>

12:16.437 --> 12:18.372
<i>Do you think you can
go to bed soon?</i>

12:19.473 --> 12:21.141
Yes, I probably should.

12:21.175 --> 12:23.911
I'm supposed to get
an endoscopy tomorrow morning.

12:23.944 --> 12:25.412
I forgot to tell you about that.

12:26.947 --> 12:28.925
They didn't let me eat
or drink anything for dinner,

12:28.949 --> 12:30.951
so I'm quite hungry and thirsty.

12:30.985 --> 12:33.465
You can probably hear my stomach
growling louder than my voice.

12:37.091 --> 12:38.492
<i>Mm. Mm.</i>

12:38.526 --> 12:40.828
<i>That's good.
You should get some sleep.</i>

12:40.861 --> 12:42.863
Oh, okay.

12:42.896 --> 12:44.298
<i>Good night, sweetheart.</i>

12:44.331 --> 12:46.166
Good night, Peter.

12:52.206 --> 12:54.141
We're sending you home.

12:55.142 --> 12:56.877
So there's nothing
wrong with me?

12:56.910 --> 13:00.014
No, there most definitely
is something wrong with you,

13:00.047 --> 13:02.182
but while we wait
for the current round of tests

13:02.216 --> 13:05.252
to come back,
there's nothing more to be done.

13:05.486 --> 13:09.390
You'd be better off being around
your family and friends.

13:10.090 --> 13:11.425
I haven't told my mom yet.

13:11.458 --> 13:13.193
I wanted to wait until
I had a better idea

13:13.227 --> 13:14.461
of what was happening.

13:14.495 --> 13:16.196
I feel much better, actually.

13:16.230 --> 13:17.998
Maybe I'm getting better.

13:18.032 --> 13:20.901
Sarah, listen very carefully.

13:20.934 --> 13:23.237
We may be in the dark here
on what exactly

13:23.270 --> 13:26.407
is happening inside of you,
but whatever it is,

13:26.440 --> 13:28.309
it's very serious.

13:29.043 --> 13:31.378
When you go home,
you need to rest.

13:31.412 --> 13:33.380
You need to take
care of yourself.

13:34.081 --> 13:36.283
You need to not drink.

13:37.151 --> 13:38.520
Do you understand?

13:40.254 --> 13:41.455
I understand.

13:42.990 --> 13:44.458
<i>Very good.</i>

13:46.994 --> 13:49.430
<i>That's very, very good.</i>

14:28.268 --> 14:30.137
<i>Hey, it's Peter.
Leave a message.</i>

15:37.104 --> 15:38.372
<i>Hey, sweetheart.</i>

15:38.405 --> 15:40.073
Guess what I just did?

15:40.107 --> 15:41.475
<i>I'm not sure. Tell me.</i>

15:41.509 --> 15:43.277
I just went to the gym.

15:43.310 --> 15:45.489
The doctor told me to rest,
but I woke up feeling energized,

15:45.513 --> 15:47.314
and so I decided
to go and work out,

15:47.347 --> 15:49.416
and I got very sweaty and hot,

15:49.450 --> 15:51.251
so the second I walked
through the door,

15:51.285 --> 15:53.220
I took off all my clothes.

15:58.125 --> 16:00.528
I actually feel a lot better
than I have in a long time.

16:00.562 --> 16:03.464
I don't think I'm sick anymore.
It was probably just a cold.

16:03.497 --> 16:04.775
I looked up the symptoms online,

16:04.799 --> 16:06.967
and that was one of
the possibilities.

16:07.535 --> 16:08.670
What's wrong?

16:13.140 --> 16:16.678
<i>You... You have a rare
condition, and it's terminal.</i>

16:17.411 --> 16:20.347
You're just imagining the worst.
I'm fine, I promise.

16:20.715 --> 16:22.550
<i>You accidentally
put my number down</i>

16:22.584 --> 16:25.452
<i>on the primary contact
instead of emergency contacts,</i>

16:25.486 --> 16:27.387
<i>so your doctor's
been calling me,</i>

16:27.421 --> 16:29.456
<i>but I assumed it was
a telemarketer,</i>

16:29.490 --> 16:31.358
<i>so I didn't answer.</i>

16:31.391 --> 16:33.528
<i>She must have assumed that
you're screening your calls</i>

16:33.561 --> 16:36.531
<i>because she left a very
detailed voicemail in my inbox.</i>

16:42.504 --> 16:44.572
You're telling me
this on video chat?

16:45.205 --> 16:47.274
<i>I know. I'm sorry.</i>

16:49.711 --> 16:51.613
How long have you known?

16:53.581 --> 16:56.651
<i>Two days.
I didn't know how to tell you.</i>

17:00.320 --> 17:02.289
<i>Sarah, you're going to die.</i>

17:08.730 --> 17:10.632
Why aren't I crying?

17:17.204 --> 17:19.674
I apologize for the voicemail.

17:21.141 --> 17:23.210
If we could keep this mix-up

17:23.242 --> 17:25.311
from making its way
to the board of directors,

17:25.345 --> 17:27.281
I would appreciate it.

17:28.415 --> 17:30.250
Sure, that's fine.

17:30.618 --> 17:35.590
So, yes, you have an incredibly
rare incurable disease.

17:36.256 --> 17:37.725
It is inside your stomach,

17:37.759 --> 17:40.728
but will eventually spread
throughout your body.

17:40.762 --> 17:44.331
It will be painless,
but it is killing you.

17:44.632 --> 17:46.601
We cannot know how
long you have,

17:46.634 --> 17:49.604
but it is only a matter of time.

17:53.641 --> 17:55.275
What are my chances?

17:56.644 --> 17:58.211
Zero.

17:58.245 --> 17:59.747
There's a 98% chance

17:59.781 --> 18:02.382
you will succumb
to your illness.

18:03.518 --> 18:05.352
I thought you said
there isn't a chance.

18:05.385 --> 18:06.554
There isn't.

18:06.588 --> 18:08.388
Then what about the two percent?

18:08.422 --> 18:12.359
That's the margin of error.
There's a 2% margin of error.

18:12.392 --> 18:14.461
Nothing is ever
absolutely certain,

18:14.494 --> 18:16.798
though this most certainly is.

18:18.600 --> 18:21.335
You're telling me there is a
margin of error of two percent,

18:21.368 --> 18:23.470
but you're certain
I'm definitely going to die?

18:23.504 --> 18:24.672
Yes.

18:25.372 --> 18:26.708
Unfortunately.

18:27.642 --> 18:30.645
You're taking this quite well,
I might add.

18:30.678 --> 18:34.181
Most people cry
when doctors give them bad news,

18:34.214 --> 18:37.184
which is why most
doctors are depressed.

18:38.686 --> 18:40.521
I don't want to die,

18:40.555 --> 18:42.523
but it sounds like
it's not up to me.

18:43.625 --> 18:45.793
To use a baseball analogy,

18:45.827 --> 18:48.462
life has thrown
you a curve ball.

18:48.830 --> 18:52.199
Curve balls are tricky throws
for the batter to hit.

18:52.232 --> 18:54.334
In this case, you're the batter.

18:54.702 --> 18:58.338
Only, you're not even holding
a bat, so you most definitely

18:58.372 --> 19:00.675
are going to miss the ball.

19:02.476 --> 19:04.712
What's next?
What are my options?

19:05.647 --> 19:08.783
You should decide on
what type of funeral you want.

19:08.816 --> 19:11.418
It usually depends
on one's religious views,

19:11.451 --> 19:15.322
but it can also be a reflection
of your personality.

19:15.623 --> 19:18.626
For example, I know
I want to be buried,

19:18.660 --> 19:20.494
not because I'm religious,

19:20.528 --> 19:24.666
but because I'm afraid
of being forgotten.

19:24.699 --> 19:27.802
I want my friends and family
to feel obligated

19:27.835 --> 19:29.704
to come and visit my grave.

19:31.338 --> 19:32.807
Of course, there are the remains

19:32.840 --> 19:35.643
from a cremation
that can be buried or interred,

19:35.677 --> 19:40.447
but people are less likely
to visit a pile of ashes.

19:40.648 --> 19:44.384
A body in a casket holds
more of an obligation.

19:44.886 --> 19:46.821
You can even be buried at sea,

19:46.854 --> 19:49.590
though that's usually
reserved for sailors.

19:49.891 --> 19:52.527
There are many options
to choose from.

19:55.663 --> 19:59.499
I'll probably choose...
cremation.

20:01.836 --> 20:04.739
Then there is the decision
of whether or not

20:04.772 --> 20:07.675
you want to go ahead
with replacement.

20:08.442 --> 20:12.479
I'm sure you're already
familiar with the process.

20:12.513 --> 20:14.582
When you know
you're going to die,

20:14.615 --> 20:16.483
you can have yourself cloned

20:16.517 --> 20:20.487
so that your loved ones won't
have to suffer the loss of you.

20:20.521 --> 20:23.624
Here's a pamphlet, just in case.

20:23.658 --> 20:25.325
Thank you.

20:25.358 --> 20:28.462
Remember to discuss it
with your loved ones first.

20:28.495 --> 20:30.631
Replacement isn't for everyone.

20:30.665 --> 20:34.434
For some families, it has even
been a negative experience.

20:34.802 --> 20:37.538
- Can I have this?
- Please.

20:59.359 --> 21:01.562
<i>Hi, there. My name is Tom.</i>

21:01.596 --> 21:04.364
<i>I'm the head West Coast
media relations officer</i>

21:04.397 --> 21:05.867
<i>here at The Facility.</i>

21:05.900 --> 21:07.835
<i>I'll be your host
for this introduction</i>

21:07.869 --> 21:09.871
<i>to the world of replacement.</i>

21:10.437 --> 21:12.540
<i>Of course, we all know
that cloning began dur...</i>

21:12.573 --> 21:14.407
<i>Our scientists have made</i>

21:14.441 --> 21:17.444
<i>countless exciting
breakthroughs and advances</i>

21:17.477 --> 21:19.914
<i>in The Facility's
proprietary technology.</i>

21:21.448 --> 21:23.416
<i>It's hard to imagine
that, at one point,</i>

21:23.450 --> 21:25.385
<i>this all seemed like
absurd science fiction.</i>

21:25.418 --> 21:26.854
<i>This period is known</i>

21:26.888 --> 21:28.656
<i>as "imprintation".</i>

21:28.689 --> 21:31.826
<i>Your double is more or less
a sponge at this point.</i>

21:33.460 --> 21:36.463
<i>They will soak up as much
of what makes you "you"</i>

21:36.496 --> 21:38.800
<i>as they can before you die.</i>

21:42.503 --> 21:44.505
<i>Down to the littlest detail.</i>

21:47.474 --> 21:50.443
<i>The more time your double
spends learning about you,</i>

21:50.477 --> 21:52.613
the more "you" they will become.

21:59.854 --> 22:01.756
<i>In some cases, however,</i>

22:01.789 --> 22:04.859
<i>your double may only have
a very short time with you.</i>

22:04.892 --> 22:08.428
<i>Such as in the case
of premeditated suicide.</i>

22:10.698 --> 22:13.466
<i>For originals who are very sad,</i>

22:13.500 --> 22:15.435
<i>everyday living is a struggle.</i>

22:17.004 --> 22:19.807
<i>This double may look
just like his original,</i>

22:19.841 --> 22:22.944
<i>but he may as well be
a different person altogether.</i>

22:22.977 --> 22:26.446
<i>For some grieving families,
this is sufficient.</i>

22:27.715 --> 22:30.852
<i>I hope you found this video
fun and informative.</i>

22:30.885 --> 22:33.486
<i>You may be dying,
but don't let that affect</i>

22:33.521 --> 22:35.022
<i>those who love you most.</i>

22:35.056 --> 22:37.592
<i>Replacement is a gift to them.</i>

22:37.925 --> 22:39.694
<i>Isn't that right, darling?</i>

22:41.662 --> 22:43.030
<i>That's right.</i>

22:43.064 --> 22:44.899
<i>I'm a former double,</i>

22:44.932 --> 22:47.702
<i>going on 12 years of being Tom.</i>

22:50.838 --> 22:52.840
<i>Replacement works.</i>

23:09.891 --> 23:11.893
Hi, I'm currently dying

23:11.926 --> 23:14.595
and I would like
to schedule a consultation.

24:05.746 --> 24:07.581
Ma'am, I'm sorry,
I forgot to ask you

24:07.615 --> 24:09.617
for some sort of
proof you're dying.

24:09.650 --> 24:11.061
They should have
mentioned that on the phone

24:11.085 --> 24:12.753
when you scheduled
your appointment.

24:12.787 --> 24:15.589
Yes, they told me. I have a copy
of my hospital charts.

24:15.623 --> 24:17.792
I can have my doctor fax
a note too if necessary.

24:17.825 --> 24:19.226
No, the charts will do.

24:19.260 --> 24:21.038
I'm still not sure
I'm going to go through with it.

24:21.062 --> 24:23.106
I'd like to talk to someone
first, if that's all right.

24:23.130 --> 24:25.533
Of course. You still have
to fill out the form, though.

24:25.566 --> 24:27.234
Of course.

24:30.171 --> 24:32.073
There's no way
I can afford this.

24:32.773 --> 24:35.977
You must understand that this
is a gift for your loved ones.

24:36.677 --> 24:39.113
Can you put a price on them
not having to be sad?

24:40.081 --> 24:41.983
You're going to die.

24:42.016 --> 24:45.853
And we understand and are
sensitive to that inevitability.

24:45.886 --> 24:48.155
What we do is we set up
a payment plan.

24:48.189 --> 24:51.692
When you pass away
and your double becomes you,

24:51.726 --> 24:53.861
they take over
your responsibilities,

24:53.894 --> 24:55.696
and one of those
responsibilities

24:55.730 --> 24:57.932
is to keep paying
off the procedure.

24:58.799 --> 25:00.167
The most important thing is

25:00.201 --> 25:02.803
that you don't have
to worry about anything.

25:03.704 --> 25:05.639
Other than dying with dignity.

25:08.142 --> 25:11.112
I'm afraid of needles,
and I sometimes have nightmares

25:11.145 --> 25:12.546
of being put under anesthesia

25:12.580 --> 25:14.682
but waking up during
the surgery.

25:16.684 --> 25:18.686
All you have to do
is spit into this.

25:19.653 --> 25:21.122
How long does it all take?

25:21.155 --> 25:22.723
About an hour.

25:24.825 --> 25:26.127
Can I get you a refill?

25:26.160 --> 25:27.962
Yes, please, but only half.

25:27.995 --> 25:29.663
I don't need a whole glass.

25:47.014 --> 25:48.182
Hello.

25:49.650 --> 25:51.085
Hi. You must be Sarah.

25:51.118 --> 25:52.953
I caught a glimpse
of myself in the mirror,

25:52.987 --> 25:54.688
and I look a lot like you.

25:55.856 --> 25:57.892
Yes, I'm Sarah.

26:01.929 --> 26:05.099
So, Sarah is your original.

26:05.132 --> 26:08.702
For now, you'll go by the name
Sarah's Double.

26:08.736 --> 26:10.938
When you replace her,
you'll take her name.

26:13.274 --> 26:15.009
You have very clean skin.

26:15.242 --> 26:17.278
And your hair shines
in the light better than mine.

26:21.015 --> 26:22.683
I like your shirt.

26:24.785 --> 26:26.720
I should tell you
that there was an error

26:26.754 --> 26:28.689
in the coding process.

26:28.722 --> 26:30.658
It affected the gene
that determines eye color.

26:31.692 --> 26:34.128
We're happy to decommission
this double and try again

26:34.161 --> 26:35.896
if you'd like.

26:37.965 --> 26:40.000
Oh, no. That won't be necessary.

26:40.034 --> 26:41.836
Blue eyes are less common
and more interesting

26:41.869 --> 26:43.337
than brown eyes.

26:43.370 --> 26:45.706
Great. We'll give you
a five-percent discount

26:45.739 --> 26:48.008
on the process to
make it up to you.

26:48.042 --> 26:50.277
Oh, that would be wonderful.

26:52.046 --> 26:53.781
Before he put me in these
temporary clothes,

26:53.814 --> 26:55.249
the technician made a joke to me

26:55.282 --> 26:57.184
about how now he's
seen you naked.

26:59.053 --> 27:00.754
Are you hungry?

27:00.788 --> 27:02.990
Not right now.

27:03.023 --> 27:04.725
What are some
of your favorite foods?

27:07.862 --> 27:09.897
I like Mexican food,

27:09.930 --> 27:13.334
Japanese food
and also Indian food.

27:14.735 --> 27:16.137
I can't wait to try those, then.

27:16.170 --> 27:18.706
What is your least
favorite kind of food?

27:19.807 --> 27:21.447
That's a good question.
Maybe French food.

27:21.475 --> 27:23.177
It can be quite heavy.

27:23.210 --> 27:25.279
Is there
a style of music you like best?

27:26.113 --> 27:27.381
I like all kinds of music,

27:27.414 --> 27:29.350
particularly pop, rock,
and hip-hop.

27:29.383 --> 27:32.019
Would you like to
listen any of those right now?

27:32.052 --> 27:34.021
Maybe later.
I'm enjoying this conversation,

27:34.054 --> 27:36.056
and music might make it
hard to hear each other.

27:36.790 --> 27:39.827
Are there any styles of music
you don't like so much?

27:40.227 --> 27:41.729
Country.

27:42.229 --> 27:43.731
And Metal.

27:44.098 --> 27:45.733
It's just a bunch of noise.

27:58.779 --> 28:00.247
Welcome home.

28:00.281 --> 28:03.083
It's nice.
Do you live here alone?

28:03.117 --> 28:05.219
No, I live here
with my boyfriend, Peter.

28:05.252 --> 28:06.787
He's away on business, though.

28:06.820 --> 28:08.198
He won't be back
for several more weeks.

28:08.222 --> 28:10.291
I hope I get to see him again
before I die.

28:10.958 --> 28:13.160
He's very handsome
and hard-working.

28:13.827 --> 28:16.797
He sounds like it.
I'm excited to meet him.

28:16.830 --> 28:18.832
I'll introduce you
to my mom, too.

28:18.866 --> 28:20.100
What about your dad?

28:20.367 --> 28:22.169
He passed away a few years ago.

28:22.870 --> 28:25.906
50 percent of marriages
end in divorce, but...

28:25.940 --> 28:27.975
my parents were still together
when he died.

28:28.008 --> 28:29.777
I never saw them fight.

28:30.044 --> 28:31.812
I know she misses him.

28:31.845 --> 28:33.847
I'm excited to meet your mom.

28:35.216 --> 28:37.184
I haven't told
her about you yet.

28:37.218 --> 28:39.253
I haven't told Peter either,
but I'm going to.

28:39.286 --> 28:41.922
Actually, I'm not sure I want
my mom to know I'm sick.

28:41.956 --> 28:43.324
I'm afraid she'll be sad.

28:43.357 --> 28:45.025
I'm her only child.

28:45.059 --> 28:46.360
When you're gone,

28:46.393 --> 28:48.395
I promise to love her
as much as you do.

28:48.429 --> 28:49.997
Maybe more.

28:50.030 --> 28:51.265
Same for Peter.

28:51.298 --> 28:53.067
I will love him so much.

28:54.201 --> 28:55.903
Let's get some clothes for you.

29:07.348 --> 29:10.351
You don't have any cellulite
or love handles.

29:12.186 --> 29:14.154
I guess I don't have
either of those things.

29:14.188 --> 29:15.322
You're right.

29:16.323 --> 29:18.225
Feels slightly loose on me.

29:20.027 --> 29:22.062
I may be a size
smaller than you.

29:22.096 --> 29:23.440
You should probably
take me shopping.

29:23.464 --> 29:25.332
What's your favorite
sexual position?

29:26.433 --> 29:29.169
Um, it's boring,
but I like missionary.

29:29.937 --> 29:32.239
Sometimes, it's nice
to be choked. Lightly.

29:32.873 --> 29:34.441
What's Peter's
favorite position?

29:36.176 --> 29:38.178
He likes standing
both from behind

29:38.212 --> 29:41.215
and facing each other,
and he likes to blindfold me,

29:41.248 --> 29:43.183
but I like to be able
to see him, though.

29:43.217 --> 29:45.319
Sure, but I imagine
not being able to see

29:45.352 --> 29:47.021
heightens the other senses.

29:47.054 --> 29:49.857
You know, I don't think
I care for this top.

29:49.890 --> 29:52.450
Maybe when you take me shopping,
I'll look for a different style.

29:58.432 --> 30:01.068
Sweetheart,
have you seen my shoes?

30:01.101 --> 30:03.137
Uh, are they these black ones?

30:03.170 --> 30:04.905
No, those are Sarah's.

30:04.938 --> 30:08.309
Mine are tan and
more fashionable.

30:08.342 --> 30:10.010
Never mind. I found them.

30:10.044 --> 30:12.079
They were by the door
where I usually leave them.

30:12.112 --> 30:14.081
Wow, sweetheart,

30:14.114 --> 30:16.250
you look beautiful.

30:16.950 --> 30:19.253
So do you.

30:27.194 --> 30:29.163
Which restaurant
are we going to?

30:29.196 --> 30:31.965
We are going
to a French brasserie.

30:31.999 --> 30:33.967
French food is my favorite.

30:36.970 --> 30:38.238
Oh, hey, Sarah.

30:38.272 --> 30:40.040
Sorry, I didn't see you there.

30:40.074 --> 30:42.009
Peter and I are going on a date.

30:42.042 --> 30:44.512
I think we all knew there was
something between Peter and me.

30:44.546 --> 30:47.314
So, it's nice
to just be open about it.

30:47.348 --> 30:49.249
I really value your friendship.

30:49.283 --> 30:50.951
I'll miss that when you die.

30:50.984 --> 30:53.487
Speaking of which, any updates?

30:56.290 --> 30:58.125
I have a doctor's
appointment tomorrow.

30:58.158 --> 31:00.260
Honey, we should hurry,
or we're going to be late.

31:00.294 --> 31:01.495
Okay.

31:04.031 --> 31:06.534
Peter and I will probably make
love when we get home tonight.

31:06.568 --> 31:10.070
As you know, I tend to be loud,
so I wanted you to be aware.

31:19.279 --> 31:21.315
Please, come in.

31:22.049 --> 31:23.317
Have a seat.

31:26.086 --> 31:27.421
How are you feeling?

31:27.454 --> 31:29.289
I feel okay.

31:29.323 --> 31:31.301
It's been completely painless,
just as you said it would be.

31:31.325 --> 31:33.160
The worst part has
been the waiting.

31:33.193 --> 31:35.062
I know it's coming,
but I don't know when.

31:35.462 --> 31:37.231
I go to sleep every
night thinking,

31:37.264 --> 31:39.567
"Maybe tomorrow will be
the day I don't wake up."

31:39.601 --> 31:42.069
I'd rather die in my sleep
than die awake.

31:42.102 --> 31:44.371
I'd rather not be able
to feel it happening.

31:44.405 --> 31:47.274
Sarah, I don't know
how to tell you this,

31:47.307 --> 31:50.043
other than direct
and to the point.

31:51.111 --> 31:53.247
You've gone into
complete remission.

31:54.214 --> 31:56.150
You're not dying anymore.

31:58.218 --> 32:00.120
You told me it was certain.

32:00.154 --> 32:03.123
I did mention
the margin of error.

32:04.091 --> 32:05.492
Are you sure?

32:05.527 --> 32:07.595
My stomach is hurting
a little bit right now.

32:07.629 --> 32:10.397
Did you have anything to
eat for breakfast this morning?

32:11.398 --> 32:13.033
No.

32:13.066 --> 32:15.235
You're most likely
just hungry, then.

32:16.103 --> 32:17.404
I don't understand.

32:18.071 --> 32:21.341
To be perfectly honest,
we don't either.

32:21.375 --> 32:23.611
But it seems
you've recovered completely

32:23.645 --> 32:26.013
and there's no reason
to think you can't live

32:26.046 --> 32:27.448
a long, fulfilling life.

32:28.650 --> 32:31.018
Your family will be thrilled.

32:32.453 --> 32:34.388
I never told my mom.

32:34.421 --> 32:36.023
Why not?

32:36.056 --> 32:37.725
I didn't want her to worry.

32:37.759 --> 32:40.327
My double was going to take over
like nothing ever happened.

32:40.360 --> 32:42.095
With contact lenses, of course.

32:42.129 --> 32:43.464
She wouldn't have to miss me.

32:44.264 --> 32:46.133
You should see The Facility

32:46.166 --> 32:48.101
about having your double
decommissioned.

32:48.135 --> 32:51.104
By law, the only people
who are allowed doubles

32:51.138 --> 32:52.473
are people who are dying,

32:52.507 --> 32:55.275
and you are no longer
one of those people.

33:44.458 --> 33:46.326
We actually went roller-skating.

33:47.327 --> 33:49.631
Oh, it was fun.
I fell, didn't I?

33:49.664 --> 33:52.132
Very badly, but it was fun.

33:52.165 --> 33:55.302
I used to roller skate.
With your father.

33:55.335 --> 33:56.738
Oh.

33:59.139 --> 34:00.608
You introduced her to my mom?

34:00.642 --> 34:02.175
Sarah, what's going on?

34:02.209 --> 34:03.545
Mom, I'm Sarah.

34:06.714 --> 34:08.447
You agreed to wait until I died

34:08.482 --> 34:10.384
before you introduced her
to my mom as me.

34:10.417 --> 34:11.686
Died?

34:11.719 --> 34:13.621
I didn't introduce
your double to your mom.

34:13.655 --> 34:16.558
She's been in contact with her
on her own for months now.

34:17.190 --> 34:19.126
You're pretending to be me?

34:19.159 --> 34:21.194
While I'm still alive,
you're talking to her?

34:21.228 --> 34:22.597
Someone had to.

34:22.630 --> 34:24.532
All your mother wanted
was a call here and there

34:24.565 --> 34:26.233
from the daughter she loves.

34:26.266 --> 34:28.735
Sarah, will one of you
please tell me what's happening?

34:28.770 --> 34:30.337
I was dying.

34:30.370 --> 34:32.371
I had a disease
that was killing me,

34:32.406 --> 34:34.274
and so, I decided
to get a replacement

34:34.308 --> 34:35.748
so that you wouldn't
have to miss me.

34:36.443 --> 34:38.210
Why didn't you tell me?

34:38.513 --> 34:40.681
I know. I did this for you.

34:40.715 --> 34:42.516
It was supposed to
be a nice gift.

34:44.752 --> 34:46.554
How much longer do you have?

34:48.523 --> 34:50.489
That's the thing.

34:50.525 --> 34:52.359
It's almost funny.

34:52.391 --> 34:54.293
I did all of this for nothing.

34:55.797 --> 34:57.297
What do you mean?

34:58.800 --> 35:01.234
I'm not going to die after all.

35:01.268 --> 35:03.504
I just left my doctor's office,
and I'm in remission.

35:04.438 --> 35:06.373
You're going to be
decommissioned.

35:08.543 --> 35:10.277
And we can go back
to being together

35:10.310 --> 35:12.212
and everything can
go back to normal.

35:14.414 --> 35:15.626
What do you mean decommissioned?

35:15.650 --> 35:16.884
Don't worry, Mother.

35:16.918 --> 35:18.519
No, don't you fucking
talk to her.

35:18.553 --> 35:21.321
You're done. I am going
to fucking abort you!

35:21.355 --> 35:23.457
- All right, come on.
- I'm Sarah, not you.

35:23.490 --> 35:25.292
You're nothing. You're no one.

35:25.325 --> 35:27.695
Come on, let's go outside.

35:39.339 --> 35:41.676
You're not kissing me.
Here, try again.

35:41.709 --> 35:43.778
- Eh... What are you doing?
- What do you mean?

35:44.712 --> 35:46.246
I'm with her now.

35:46.581 --> 35:47.815
Didn't you hear me?

35:47.849 --> 35:49.684
She's going to be
decommissioned.

35:49.717 --> 35:52.687
So... we can go back
to you and me.

35:52.720 --> 35:54.488
It's not that simple.

35:56.591 --> 35:58.325
What is it about her?

36:00.460 --> 36:02.262
It's little things.

36:02.764 --> 36:04.632
Like her inflection
when she says my name.

36:04.666 --> 36:07.769
Hers goes up. Peter!
Yours is flat. Peter.

36:08.736 --> 36:10.772
I can say your name
that way if you want.

36:11.405 --> 36:14.341
Just tell me what you want me
to be, and I'll be it for you.

36:16.744 --> 36:19.312
You always try too hard
to impress new people.

36:19.346 --> 36:20.715
You speak over me or for me.

36:20.748 --> 36:23.350
You have to control
social situations.

36:23.383 --> 36:25.285
I'm embarrassed to
go out with you.

36:25.318 --> 36:26.462
Every time we go out,
my co-workers

36:26.486 --> 36:28.388
make fun of you
behind your back.

36:28.422 --> 36:30.333
That is, when I can actually
get you to leave the house,

36:30.357 --> 36:31.793
and even if I do,
it's always on me.

36:31.826 --> 36:33.928
I can't do it anymore.

36:36.363 --> 36:39.399
Even if I can't be with her,
I don't want to be with you.

36:44.337 --> 36:45.707
I love you, Peter.

36:46.741 --> 36:48.910
And no one will ever love you
as much as I do.

36:50.545 --> 36:52.312
I know.

36:52.345 --> 36:54.582
But I don't love you anymore.

36:59.319 --> 37:00.655
What's it like to fuck me

37:00.688 --> 37:02.422
while you look into
someone else's eyes?

37:05.392 --> 37:07.294
You need therapy, Sarah.

37:14.669 --> 37:16.904
Wait, this is my mom's house.

37:22.677 --> 37:24.712
Mom? Hey, Mom.

37:24.746 --> 37:26.514
Peter locked me out.

37:54.842 --> 37:58.679
I hope the decommission process
is painful for you, bitch!

37:58.713 --> 38:01.916
And I hope it's emotionally
painful for the two of you!

38:09.456 --> 38:10.691
Hello?

38:10.725 --> 38:12.359
<i>Is this Sarah?</i>

38:12.392 --> 38:13.628
Yes. Who's this?

38:13.661 --> 38:15.062
<i>I represent your double.</i>

38:15.096 --> 38:16.864
<i>This call is to notify you
that she will be</i>

38:16.898 --> 38:18.633
<i>exercising her rights
in accordance</i>

38:18.666 --> 38:20.668
<i>with the 28th Amendment
of the Constitution.</i>

38:20.701 --> 38:22.837
<i>Your double has filed
a motion to stay.</i>

38:22.870 --> 38:24.806
What do you mean "stay"?

38:24.839 --> 38:26.841
<i>I suggest you
consult with legal counsel.</i>

38:26.874 --> 38:28.643
<i>Have a nice day.</i>

38:34.982 --> 38:37.417
It's a fairly standard
motion to stay.

38:38.019 --> 38:39.854
All the usual stipulations.

38:41.488 --> 38:43.490
No contact with your double
starting immediately.

38:44.625 --> 38:46.003
Because the lease
is in your ex's name,

38:46.027 --> 38:47.662
you're being asked to move out.

38:47.695 --> 38:50.565
They're giving you two days,
which is quite generous,

38:50.598 --> 38:52.365
as usually it's only one.

38:52.399 --> 38:54.769
The duel to the death will be
in approximately one year.

38:54.802 --> 38:57.738
The exact date to be determined
by the court at a later time.

38:57.772 --> 38:59.106
And you'll be expected to pay

38:59.140 --> 39:00.708
support to your double
in the interim.

39:00.741 --> 39:02.677
Wait, did you say
duel to the death?

39:02.710 --> 39:05.012
Yes, it is to determine
which of you will live

39:05.046 --> 39:06.614
the rest of Sarah's life.

39:06.647 --> 39:07.991
We can't have two of you
walking around forever.

39:08.015 --> 39:09.617
That would be ridiculous.

39:09.650 --> 39:11.484
I thought she was going
to be decommissioned.

39:11.519 --> 39:12.887
Well, in cases such as yours,

39:12.920 --> 39:14.956
when an original is going
to live after all,

39:14.989 --> 39:17.490
the double is usually
decommissioned, yes.

39:17.525 --> 39:19.527
But, in even rarer cases,

39:19.560 --> 39:21.461
when a double has been
in the world long enough

39:21.494 --> 39:23.030
to start becoming
their own person,

39:23.064 --> 39:25.900
they sometimes would prefer
to continue to live.

39:25.933 --> 39:28.569
They can request a stay
and a duel is set.

39:28.603 --> 39:30.605
I thought the duels
were only for prisoners

39:30.638 --> 39:32.439
who commit the crime
worse than murder.

39:32.472 --> 39:34.041
They're also used for stays.

39:34.075 --> 39:35.810
Haven't even seen
one on television?

39:35.843 --> 39:37.578
They're quite popular.

39:37.945 --> 39:40.781
I don't care for violence.
It makes me nauseous.

39:40.815 --> 39:42.583
Well, you'll need
to get over that

39:42.617 --> 39:44.785
if you want any chance
of surviving your duel.

39:45.620 --> 39:48.455
I suggest taking personal
combat training lessons

39:48.488 --> 39:49.991
from a personal combat trainer.

39:50.858 --> 39:52.827
Also, we should
discuss my rates.

40:09.977 --> 40:12.647
You can take the sheets with
the giant blood stain on them.

40:12.680 --> 40:14.582
You should have
washed them in cold water.

40:14.982 --> 40:16.951
You can take anything you like.

40:16.984 --> 40:18.986
Your double has
different taste than you,

40:19.020 --> 40:20.955
and we'd like to
redecorate anyway.

40:20.988 --> 40:23.691
Maybe leave the couch, though,
and the nice coffee table.

40:23.724 --> 40:25.826
But other than that,
you can take anything you like.

40:27.728 --> 40:29.030
Hey, sweetheart!

40:29.063 --> 40:30.831
<i>Is she still there?</i>

40:30.865 --> 40:33.634
Yes, she is,
but she's going to be gone soon.

40:33.668 --> 40:35.503
<i>I'm glad I don't have to see</i>

40:35.536 --> 40:37.071
<i>her disgusting face
again for a while.</i>

40:37.772 --> 40:40.608
<i>Oh, tell her to take
the bloody sheets with her.</i>

40:41.542 --> 40:43.544
Don't worry. I already did.

40:43.577 --> 40:44.845
<i>Good.</i>

40:46.814 --> 40:47.882
<i>I miss you.</i>

40:48.549 --> 40:49.750
I miss you, too.

41:23.718 --> 41:25.786
Do you want to live?

41:28.856 --> 41:30.624
Yes.

41:32.660 --> 41:33.894
I don't believe you.

41:35.629 --> 41:37.064
I want to live.

41:37.798 --> 41:39.900
Because if you know
that you do not care

41:39.934 --> 41:41.769
if you live or die in your duel,

41:41.802 --> 41:43.771
you may as well
tell me right now.

41:43.804 --> 41:47.641
I will tear up your contract,
and you can spend all the money

41:47.675 --> 41:51.012
that you save over the next year
on drugs and alcohol,

41:51.045 --> 41:54.115
vacations to the beach, sex...

41:55.049 --> 41:57.084
trips to amusement parks.

41:58.786 --> 42:00.788
You will surely
die in your duel,

42:00.821 --> 42:02.923
but you will have lived
your last year on Earth

42:02.957 --> 42:06.027
in an excessive
and exciting fashion.

42:08.829 --> 42:10.831
I said I want to live.

42:12.967 --> 42:15.036
Are you prepared to kill?

42:17.038 --> 42:18.172
Yes.

42:20.074 --> 42:21.776
I believe you.

42:24.045 --> 42:27.214
First, we need to get
your body healthy and ready...

42:28.049 --> 42:29.683
for what's to come.

42:32.053 --> 42:34.255
We'll start with some
general calisthenics.

43:16.030 --> 43:17.131
Come on.

43:39.787 --> 43:41.222
I feel like I'm
going to throw up.

43:41.856 --> 43:44.225
It's due to all
the lactic acid in your blood.

43:44.258 --> 43:46.293
It's temporarily poisoning you.

43:47.094 --> 43:50.030
Don't worry. The feeling
will go away eventually.

43:52.867 --> 43:54.135
I'm going to live.

43:54.168 --> 43:55.836
This is my life.

43:55.870 --> 43:57.905
She's not going
to take it from me.

44:03.878 --> 44:06.013
I want you to watch
that tonight.

44:06.046 --> 44:08.782
It's not very good,
but there are some images in it

44:08.816 --> 44:10.918
that I want you
to get used to seeing.

44:12.319 --> 44:13.988
I'll see you tomorrow.

